cdx6500PPCTSPPPortTable.name: cdx6500PPCTSPPPortTable
cdx6500PPCTSPPPortTable.description: This table contains the SPP Port configuration parameters.

cdx6500PPCTSPPPortEntry.name: cdx6500PPCTSPPPortEntry
cdx6500PPCTSPPPortEntry.description: Entries in the SPP Port Configuration Table.

cdx6500SPPPCfgPortSpeed.name: cdx6500SPPPCfgPortSpeed
cdx6500SPPPCfgPortSpeed.description: This is the speed of the port in bits per second. speed300 : 300 bits per second speed600 : 600 bits per second speed1200 : 1200 bits per second speed1800 : 1800 bits per second speed2400 : 2400 bits per second speed4800 : 4800 bits per second speed7200 : 7200 bits per second speed9600 : 9600 bits per second speed19200 : 19200 bits per second.

cdx6500SPPPCfgInterchTimeout.name: cdx6500SPPPCfgInterchTimeout
cdx6500SPPPCfgInterchTimeout.description: This indicates the maximum time period allowed between received characters. time50 : maximum time period allowed 50 seconds. time100 : maximum time period allowed 100 seconds. time150 : maximum time period allowed 150 seconds. time200 : maximum time period allowed 200 seconds. time250 : maximum time period allowed 250 seconds.

cdx6500SPPPCfgSLCNum.name: cdx6500SPPPCfgSLCNum
cdx6500SPPPCfgSLCNum.description: This specifies the SLC (Smart Line Controller) the port is connected to.

cdx6500SPPPCfgSLCLineNum.name: cdx6500SPPPCfgSLCLineNum
cdx6500SPPPCfgSLCLineNum.description: This specifies the line on the SLC (Smart Line Controller) the port is connected to.

cdx6500SPPPCfgStnIDList.name: cdx6500SPPPCfgStnIDList
cdx6500SPPPCfgStnIDList.description: List of station identifiers the port will support. A range of station numbers can be entered, for example : 1, 6, 8-12, 250-255 indicates 1, 6, 8, 9, 10, 11, 12, 250, 251, 252, 253, 254, 255 .

cdx6500SPPPCfgProtocolID.name: cdx6500SPPPCfgProtocolID
cdx6500SPPPCfgProtocolID.description: The Protocol Identifier is the first four bytes of the call user data. The default is: 0x11, 0x9F, 0xA7, 0x46.

cdx6500SPPPCfgQueueSize.name: cdx6500SPPPCfgQueueSize
cdx6500SPPPCfgQueueSize.description: This specifies the size of the queue which will be used to store the packets to be forwarded to SLC (Smart Line Controller).

cdx6500SPPPCfgBlockingThresh.name: cdx6500SPPPCfgBlockingThresh
cdx6500SPPPCfgBlockingThresh.description: This specifies the blocking threshold for the queue being used by the SPP.

cdx6500SPPPCfgUnblockThresh.name: cdx6500SPPPCfgUnblockThresh
cdx6500SPPPCfgUnblockThresh.description: This specifies the unblocking threshold for the queue being used by the SPP.

cdx6500SPPPCfgElectricalInterfaceType.name: cdx6500SPPPCfgElectricalInterfaceType
cdx6500SPPPCfgElectricalInterfaceType.description: Specify the Electrical Interface Type: V.24 - V.24 Electrical Interface Type V.35 - V.35 Electrical Interface Type V.36 - V.36 Electrical Interface Type X.21 - X.21 Electrical Interface Type NONE - Electrically disabled

cdx6500SPPPCfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOpti.name: cdx6500SPPPCfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOption
cdx6500SPPPCfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOpti.description: Specify the Pin 22 option: RI - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Ring Indicator output signal TM - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Test Mode input signal

cdx6500SPPPCfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfa.name: cdx6500SPPPCfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfaceOption
cdx6500SPPPCfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfa.description: Specify the cable type: NONE - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with straight through cable XOVER - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with crossover adapter cable

cdx6500SPPPStatPortStatus.description: This indicates the operational status of the port. disabled : port is disabled enabled : port is enabled busyOut : busy out the port up : port is up down : port is down. newvalDisabled : same functionality as 'disabled', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500SPPPStatPortType.name: cdx6500SPPPStatPortType
cdx6500SPPPStatPortType.description: This indicates the type of access protocol for this port.

cdx6500SPPPStatPortSpeed.name: cdx6500SPPPStatPortSpeed
cdx6500SPPPStatPortSpeed.description: This indicates the port speed in bits per second. speed300 : 300 bits per second speed600 : 600 bits per second speed1200 : 1200 bits per second speed1800 : 1800 bits per second speed2400 : 2400 bits per second speed4800 : 4800 bits per second speed7200 : 7200 bits per second speed9600 : 9600 bits per second speed19200 : 19200 bits per second.

cdx6500SPPPStatPortUtilIn.name: cdx6500SPPPStatPortUtilIn
cdx6500SPPPStatPortUtilIn.description: This indicates the port utilization for the line to port direction.

cdx6500SPPPStatPortUtilOut.name: cdx6500SPPPStatPortUtilOut
cdx6500SPPPStatPortUtilOut.description: This indicates the port utilization for the port to line direction.

cdx6500SPPPStatSLCNum.name: cdx6500SPPPStatSLCNum
cdx6500SPPPStatSLCNum.description: This indicates the number of the SLC to which the port is connected.

cdx6500SPPPStatSLCLineNum.name: cdx6500SPPPStatSLCLineNum
cdx6500SPPPStatSLCLineNum.description: This indicates the line number of the SLC to which the port is connected.

cdx6500SPPPStatFlowCntrlState.name: cdx6500SPPPStatFlowCntrlState
cdx6500SPPPStatFlowCntrlState.description: This indicates whether the port is blocked by SLC or not.

cdx6500SPPPStatLastStatsReset.name: cdx6500SPPPStatLastStatsReset
cdx6500SPPPStatLastStatsReset.description: This specifies the time stamp of the last statistics reset.

cdx6500SPPPStatChrsIn.name: cdx6500SPPPStatChrsIn
cdx6500SPPPStatChrsIn.description: This indicates the number of characters that have been received by the port.

cdx6500SPPPStatChrsOut.name: cdx6500SPPPStatChrsOut
cdx6500SPPPStatChrsOut.description: This indicates the number of characters that have been transmitted by the port.

cdx6500SPPPStatFramesIn.name: cdx6500SPPPStatFramesIn
cdx6500SPPPStatFramesIn.description: This indicates the number of frames that have been received by the port.

cdx6500SPPPStatFramesOut.name: cdx6500SPPPStatFramesOut
cdx6500SPPPStatFramesOut.description: This indicates the number of frames that have been transmitted by the port.

cdx6500SPPPStatChrsInPerSec.name: cdx6500SPPPStatChrsInPerSec
cdx6500SPPPStatChrsInPerSec.description: This indicates the rate at which characters have been received by the port.

cdx6500SPPPStatChrsOutPerSec.name: cdx6500SPPPStatChrsOutPerSec
cdx6500SPPPStatChrsOutPerSec.description: This indicates the rate at which characters have been transmitted by the port.

cdx6500SPPPStatFramesInPerSec.name: cdx6500SPPPStatFramesInPerSec
cdx6500SPPPStatFramesInPerSec.description: This indicates the rate at which frames have been received by the port.

cdx6500SPPPStatFramesOutPerSec.name: cdx6500SPPPStatFramesOutPerSec
cdx6500SPPPStatFramesOutPerSec.description: This indicates the rate at which frames have been transmitted by the port.

cdx6500SPPPStatNoOfErrorFrames.name: cdx6500SPPPStatNoOfErrorFrames
cdx6500SPPPStatNoOfErrorFrames.description: This indicates the number of erroneous frames received by the port.

cdx6500SPPPStatNoOfStns.name: cdx6500SPPPStatNoOfStns
cdx6500SPPPStatNoOfStns.description: This indicates the number of stations on this SLC line.

cdx6500SPPSStatStnStatus.description: This indicates the state of the station. disabled : Station is disabled enabled : Station is enabled busyOut : busy out the station up : Station is enabled down : Station is down. newvalDisabled : same functionality as 'disabled', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.
